alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 07 at 8:03AM PST until December 07 at 9:49PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. Chehalis River Above Grand Mound affecting Thurston and Grays Harbor Counties. ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Chehalis River At Porter affecting Grays Harbor County. .Light rain will continue to move over the region today but is not expected to impact flood levels. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River near Carnation. * WHEN...Until late this evening. * IMPACTS...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:45 AM PST Thursday the stage was 54.2 feet. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:45 AM PST Thursday was 56.7 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage late this morning and continue falling. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 54.2 feet on 02/15/1997. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this afternoon at 415 PM PST.
